<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>England's long-awaited return is finally over as Gareth Southgate's men take on Iceland in their first Nations League clash this evening.</p>

<p>The Three Lions will be targeting a strong start in Group B after the lengthy wait for their first international clash of the year - and a host of uncapped players, including Phil Foden, may feature at senior level for the first time.</p>

<p>Southgate will be wary of suffering another shock defeat to Iceland after the humiliation at Euro 2016 with Denmark still to come on Tuesday. </p>

<p>Follow all the latest updates, including the score, line-ups and build-up, right here with Sportsmail. </p>
